##Individual Report – Nancy Erichsen

At the beginning of this DevOps project, I contributed by evaluating the current
development process at Auby and Brich Finance, using the background information
provided in the assignment. I also co-created an initial draft of the presentation with a
fellow student. The presentation was later revised multiple times by other team
members.
I was primarily responsible for developing and testing the Kubernetes YAML files,
enabling the application to run in a Kubernetes cluster with PostgreSQL and fetch
Docker images from GitLab. This also included setting up namespaces, configuring an
init-db file, defining secrets, and creating the necessary services for the components to
communicate properly within the cluster.
Additionally, I wrote parts of the setup guide and process documentation, particularly
related to the Kubernetes setup and its functionality. Toward the end, I contributed to the
final presentation set up and recorded my section for the audio used in the presentation.
Like the other group members, I actively participated in meetings where we made joint
decisions and worked together to find effective solutions for the project.
